# Error Resolution Log

## When to Log

Log to ERROR_FIX_LOG.md when resolving:

- Build failures (Unity, Board SDK)
- Runtime errors (NullReference, missing pieces, etc.)
- File I/O errors (log write failures)
- Board Simulator or device-specific issues
- Anything that took >5 minutes to diagnose

## When NOT to Log

- Typos, linter warnings
- Expected test failures
- Minor refactors

## Log Format

| Date | Error | Context | Root Cause | Fix | Prevention |

## Category Prefixes (for this project)

- `[Unity]` — Engine, project setup
- `[Board]` — Board SDK, Simulator, piece input
- `[C#]` — Game logic, null refs, threading
- `[IO]` — Log file, persistentDataPath
- `[Build]` — Sideload, packaging
